      "components": [],
      "definition": "Innovation that originates from frontline employees or teams rather than from senior leadership or dedicated R&D functions.",
      "what_it_really_means": "Innovation from the people closest to the work. Bottom-up innovation often produces the most practically grounded ideas because those generating them understand the constraints and opportunities that leadership does not see.",
