      "definition": "A plan designed to take a possible future event or circumstance into account, outlining actions to be taken if specific conditions occur.",
      "what_it_really_means": "What organizations produce after something went wrong. Real contingency plans identify the risk in advance, define the response before the moment arrives, and specify the condition that activates the response. Most organizations skip at least one of the three.",
