      "definition": "The desired condition or outcome an organization is working toward, typically described in sufficient detail that progress can be evaluated against it.",
      "what_it_really_means": "What organizations sketch on whiteboards during planning sessions. Real future state requires a timeframe and indicators. Without them, the future state is indistinguishable from wishful thinking.",
      "why": "Timeframe and measurable indicators are grouped because one without the other cannot be evaluated. A target without a timeframe is aspirational. A timeframe without indicators cannot be confirmed or disconfirmed.",
