      "definition": "The creation of an independent company by separating a business unit or division from its parent organization.",
      "what_it_really_means": "A divestiture that creates a new, standalone entity rather than selling to an existing one. Spin-offs are used when the separated business is believed to be worth more independently than as part of the parent.",
      "why": "Points to Transition Management. A spin-off is a specific transition mechanism for separating a business unit.",
      "alternatives": [],
      "is_metaphor": true
