      "definition": "The ability of an organization to quickly recognize and respond to strategic opportunities and threats by adjusting direction without losing momentum.",
      "what_it_really_means": "Advantageous positioning maintained through adaptability. Strategic agility is the capacity to shift position quickly when the market or competitive landscape changes — preserving the advantage by not being locked into the position that produced it.",
      "why": "Points to Advantageous Positioning. Strategic agility is the dynamic capability that enables an organization to maintain or achieve advantageous positioning over time.",
