      "definition": "Strategic direction that originates from senior leadership and flows down through the organization.",
      "what_it_really_means": "The traditional model of leadership-driven strategy. Top-down direction has clarity and speed on its side. It produces alignment when the direction is right and misalignment when it is not — because there is no mechanism to surface disagreement from below.",
      "why": "Points to Visionary Leadership. Top-down direction is the operational expression of visionary leadership applied through organizational hierarchy.",
