      "formula": "Quiet Quitting = (presence - discretionary effort) + minimum compliance",
      "components": [
        "presence",
        "discretionary effort",
        "minimum compliance"
      ],
      "definition": "A workplace phenomenon in which employees do the minimum required by their role without formally resigning, withdrawing extra effort and emotional investment.",
      "what_it_really_means": "Showing up without showing up. The employee is present. Their commitment is not. The term became popular but the thing itself is old. It usually signals a broken employment relationship, not a lazy employee. Most people who quiet quit were once willing to give more.",
      "why": "Discretionary effort is subtracted first. That is the defining feature of the dynamic. What remains is presence without investment. Minimum compliance is not the same as resignation. It is disengagement that hasn't reached the point of leaving. Understanding what removed the discretionary effort matters more than naming the behavior.",
