      "definition": "Performance or behavioral feedback delivered close to the moment of the action or event it addresses.",
      "what_it_really_means": "Feedback given while it still matters. Most feedback is given too late to change anything. Real-time feedback works when it is specific, immediate, and tells the person what to do differently. Vague feedback delivered instantly is just noise with urgency attached.",
