      "definition": "The process of restructuring an organization's workforce to match current operational needs, often resulting in headcount reductions.",
      "what_it_really_means": "A polite word for layoffs. Occasionally it means adding roles where gaps exist. Mostly it means cutting them where surplus does. The word was invented to soften what is often a hard and human decision. The people being rightsized tend to use a different word for it.",
      "why": "Redundancy is subtracted first. That is the point of the exercise. What remains is workforce capacity aligned to what the organization actually needs now, not what it needed when those roles were created. Aligned structure is the condition that makes the new size functional rather than just smaller.",
