      "definition": "A leadership model that prescribes adjusting leadership style based on the competence and commitment of the individual being led.",
      "what_it_really_means": "Leadership adapted to the person and the situation. Situational leadership rejects a single leadership style in favor of one that shifts between directing, coaching, supporting, and delegating depending on what each individual needs at that moment.",
      "why": "Points to Leadership. Situational leadership is a specific model for adapting leadership approach to individual needs.",
