      "what_it_really_means": "The thing most leaders say they do and few actually do. Real organizational storytelling is not an anecdote before the slides. It is a narrative that makes the audience feel something and remember the point afterward. Most business storytelling skips the emotional truth and wonders why no one remembers it.",
      "why": "Emotional truth and clear point are grouped because both are required for the story to land and matter. Emotional truth without a clear point produces feeling without direction. A clear point without emotional truth produces a fact the audience agrees with and immediately forgets. Relatable context is what gets them in the door.",
