      "what_it_really_means": "The team that makes sure the organization always has the cash it needs and does not take on financial risks it cannot manage. Treasury is invisible when it works. When it fails — when cash runs dry, when currency exposure becomes a shock, when refinancing falls through — the organization notices immediately. It is one of the most consequential and least celebrated finance functions.",
      "why": "Funding and capital structure oversight and financial risk management are grouped because treasury without both is an incomplete function. Cash management without funding oversight produces day-to-day liquidity discipline with no view on the structural financing. Funding without risk management produces a capital structure that may be exposed to market, currency, or counterparty risks that erode its value. Together they define treasury as a complete financial stewardship function.",
