      "why": "Automatic activation without awareness and influence on judgment and behavior are grouped because unconscious bias is defined by both. An implicit attitude without automatic activation is a known preference rather than an unconscious one. Automatic activation without documented influence on behavior produces a psychological phenomenon without organizational consequence. Both together define a bias that operates invisibly and produces real decisions.",
