      "definition": "The practice of managing ongoing relationships with key customers or clients to maximize retention and revenue.",
      "what_it_really_means": "The revenue side of accounts management. While accounts payable manages obligations to suppliers, account management focuses on the commercial relationships that generate the revenue those obligations are paid from.",
      "why": "Points to Accounts Payable. Account management operates on the receivables side of the commercial relationship.",
      "alternatives": [],
