      "definition": "The additional value created by combining two organizations that exceeds what each could achieve independently.",
      "what_it_really_means": "The justification for the deal premium. Acquisition synergies are the projected cost savings or revenue gains that make paying more than the standalone value rational. The word is used expansively in M&A announcements and delivered conservatively in post-merger reality.",
      "why": "Points to Merger. Acquisition synergy is the value creation rationale that drives merger and acquisition activity.",
