      "components": [],
      "definition": "A receivable or loan that is unlikely to be collected and must be written off as a loss.",
      "what_it_really_means": "Money lent or owed that will not be recovered. Bad debt reflects the risk inherent in extending credit — some proportion of credit extended will not be repaid, and that proportion must be anticipated and managed.",
      "why": "Points to Credit Facility. Bad debt is the negative outcome of extending credit — the risk that the credit facility or receivable will not be repaid.",
