      "definition": "Spending on acquiring, upgrading, or maintaining long-term physical or intangible assets.",
      "what_it_really_means": "Capital deployed into assets with long useful lives. Capital expenditure — CAPEX — is capitalized on the balance sheet and depreciated over time, rather than expensed immediately. Decisions about CAPEX determine what the organization will have the capacity to do in future periods.",
      "why": "Points to Capital. Capital expenditure is a specific deployment of capital into long-term assets.",
      "alternatives": [],
