      "status": "alternative",
      "primary": "Working Capital",
      "formula_type": null,
      "formula": "See: Working Capital",
      "components": [],
      "definition": "The average number of days an organization takes to pay its suppliers after receiving a bill.",
      "what_it_really_means": "How long the organization holds on to its cash before paying suppliers. Longer DPO extends working capital by keeping cash in the business longer. Too long damages supplier relationships and credit terms.",
      "why": "Points to Working Capital. DPO is one component of the cash conversion cycle that determines working capital levels.",
