      "formula": "See: Valuation",
      "components": [],
      "definition": "Revenue received in advance for goods or services not yet delivered, recorded as a liability until the obligation is fulfilled.",
      "what_it_really_means": "Cash received that has not yet been earned. Deferred revenue is a liability because the organization still owes the customer the product or service. Once delivered, it converts to recognized revenue.",
      "why": "Points to Valuation. Deferred revenue affects how organizations are valued — high deferred revenue signals future revenue already contracted but not yet recognized.",
      "alternatives": [],
