      "components": [],
      "definition": "The application of accounting principles and investigative techniques to disputes, fraud, litigation, or financial irregularities.",
      "what_it_really_means": "Accounting used to find what went wrong. Forensic accountants trace money through complex transactions, identify discrepancies in records, and produce findings that can hold up in legal proceedings.",
      "why": "Points to Accounts Payable. Forensic accounting investigates payable and receivable records, among others, to detect irregularities.",
