      "why": "Operational alignment and cultural consolidation are grouped because both are required and neither can wait for the other. Operational alignment without cultural consolidation produces efficient processes that people resist. Cultural consolidation without operational alignment produces unified values applied to fragmented systems. Both must be addressed simultaneously for the integration to succeed.",
