      "definition": "A systematic and independent review of records, processes, or systems to assess accuracy, compliance, or effectiveness against defined standards.",
      "what_it_really_means": "An independent check on whether what is reported matches what is real. Audits serve two functions: verification and deterrence. Knowing an audit will happen changes behavior before it does. The independence is what gives the findings credibility. An audit conducted by people with a stake in the outcome is not an audit. It is a review.",
      "why": "Evidence review and findings and conclusions are grouped because they are the substance and the output of the audit. Independent examination without evidence is assertion. Evidence without conclusions is raw data. Both together produce a finding that the organization can act on and that external parties can trust.",
