      "definition": "The total time elapsed from the start of a process or production step to its completion.",
      "what_it_really_means": "How long it actually takes to do the thing. Cycle time is the key measure in just-in-time systems — it must be matched to customer demand rate for the system to operate without excess inventory or waiting.",
      "why": "Points to Just-in-Time. Cycle time is the fundamental process performance metric in just-in-time manufacturing and service delivery.",
