      "definition": "The process of moving from a high-level view of a problem or dataset to more granular detail to identify specific causes or patterns.",
      "what_it_really_means": "Going deeper into the data or analysis. Drilling down is how surface-level observations become specific findings — the analytical move from aggregate to detail that root cause analysis depends on.",
      "why": "Points to Root Cause Analysis. Drilling down is the analytical technique used to find root causes within larger data sets or complex processes.",
      "alternatives": [],
