      "definition": "A recruiter or executive search professional who proactively identifies and approaches qualified candidates for senior or specialized roles on behalf of a client organization.",
      "what_it_really_means": "A recruiter who finds people who are not looking. Headhunters identify people already employed and performing well, and approach them about opportunities they were not seeking. The value is access to passive candidates — those who would not have applied but who are the best fit for the role. The cost is the fee, which is typically significant.",
      "why": "Proactive candidate sourcing and match to defined role requirements are grouped because headhunting without both is either sourcing without a target or a requirement without a search. Proactive sourcing without a defined match profile produces a candidate pool with no quality filter. A defined requirement without proactive sourcing waits for candidates who may not exist in the active market. Together they define executive search as a targeted, active pursuit.",
