      "what_it_really_means": "Data that shows where the heat is. Heat maps compress complex data into a visual that communicates relative intensity at a glance. Risk heat maps show where risks cluster by likelihood and impact. Website heat maps show where users click or scroll. The color encoding does what tables of numbers cannot: reveal patterns without requiring the viewer to calculate them.",
