      "what_it_really_means": "Taking what works from each and combining them deliberately. Hybrid approaches are everywhere: hybrid work, hybrid methodology, hybrid pricing. The word signals intentional combination rather than indecision. The quality of a hybrid approach depends on whether the elements were chosen for a reason or assembled to avoid committing to either option fully.",
      "why": "Intentional integration is the component that distinguishes a hybrid approach from an inconsistent one. Method A and B elements without intentional integration produce a confused process rather than a combined one. Intentional integration ensures the combination is designed rather than inherited. Without it, hybrid is often a label applied to something that was not planned at all.",
