      "why": "Evidence of causation or contribution and audience-appropriate presentation are grouped because an impact report without both is either a list of activities or a polished document with no substance. Defined outcomes without evidence produce claims with no verification. Evidence without audience-appropriate presentation produces findings that fail to communicate. Together they define a report that is both substantively credible and effectively communicated.",
