      "definition": "A business function or process transferred to an external provider who performs it on behalf of the organization.",
      "what_it_really_means": "Fulfillment by an external party rather than internal operations. Outsourcing shifts execution responsibility to a provider while the organization retains accountability for the outcome. The provider fulfills what the organization has committed to.",
      "why": "Points to Fulfillment. An outsourced function is an alternative fulfillment arrangement where an external provider delivers the organizational output.",
