      "definition": "The process of identifying and qualifying potential customers for a product or service.",
      "what_it_really_means": "The front end of sales, supported by content. Prospecting involves finding people who might become customers — content management supports this by producing materials that attract and identify prospects before direct sales engagement begins.",
      "why": "Points to Content Management. Content management supports prospecting by producing content that attracts and qualifies potential customers.",
