      "components": [],
      "definition": "The creation of a preliminary model of a product or feature to test design concepts and gather feedback before full development.",
      "what_it_really_means": "Building to learn rather than building to ship. Prototypes are low-fidelity representations that enable feedback before significant investment is made. Like MVPs, they accelerate learning by making ideas testable.",
      "why": "Points to Minimum Viable Product. Prototyping is the iterative design technique that produces early versions for testing, similar in purpose to an MVP.",
      "alternatives": [],
