      "why": "Ratio formula. Deals closed alone is a volume number. Total opportunities pursued alone is pipeline size. Divided, they produce the win rate — the percentage of attempts that succeed. The ratio makes performance comparable across different pipeline sizes, time periods, and sales team configurations. A team that closes 3 of 10 is performing differently than one that closes 30 of 100, but the ratio is the same.",
