      "what_it_really_means": "How many of the people who could have done the thing actually did it. Conversion rate is used across marketing, sales, and product contexts. In e-commerce, it is purchases divided by site visitors. In lead generation, it is leads generated divided by page views. In sales, it is deals closed divided by qualified opportunities. The denominator defines what is being measured. The numerator defines what counts as success.",
      "why": "Ratio formula. Conversions alone is a count. Visitors or opportunities alone is exposure. Divided, they produce a rate that makes optimization possible. A 2% conversion rate on 10,000 visitors and a 2% conversion rate on 100,000 visitors are the same rate with very different implications for absolute volume. The ratio is what allows comparison and improvement targeting.",
