      "what_it_really_means": "The currency moved the wrong way and now the money is worth less. Organizations operating internationally face foreign exchange exposure on every transaction or balance denominated in another currency. When rates move unfavorably between when an obligation is incurred and when it is settled, the difference is a loss that hits the income statement. The exposure can be managed through hedging but never fully eliminated.",
      "why": "Converted value at settlement rate and realized loss recognition are grouped because the foreign exchange loss is defined by the gap between original value and settlement value. The converted value at settlement rate is the reality of what was received or paid. The realized loss recognition is when and how the accounting captures the shortfall. Together they define the loss as both a financial fact and an accounting event.",
