      "why": "Data-driven optimization and scalable growth mechanism are grouped because growth hacking without both is just experimentation. Rapid experimentation without data-driven optimization produces many tests with no system for identifying winners. A scalable growth mechanism without data-driven optimization produces a channel that may or may not be performing as well as it could. Together they define growth hacking as a disciplined pursuit of efficient scale.",
