      "why": "Compounding momentum and organizational strain are grouped because hyper-growth produces both simultaneously and neither can be ignored. Compounding momentum is the positive force — growth attracting talent, capital, and customers in a virtuous cycle. Organizational strain is the countervailing force that, if unmanaged, breaks the momentum. Both together define hyper-growth as an opportunity that requires active management to not become its own worst enemy.",
