      "formula": "See: Standard Process",
      "components": [],
      "definition": "A fast, high-impact improvement that can be implemented quickly with minimal effort or investment.",
      "what_it_really_means": "The low-hanging fruit of process improvement. Quick hits are improvements that the standard process can deliver immediately without significant redesign. They build momentum for larger changes by demonstrating that improvement is possible and valued.",
      "why": "Points to Standard Process. A quick hit is a rapid improvement achievable within existing standard process frameworks.",
