      "what_it_really_means": "A structured way of being honest about what you are good at, where you fall short, what the environment offers, and what could hurt you. SWOT is one of the most used and least challenging strategic tools. Its value depends entirely on the honesty with which it is completed. A SWOT that lists only impressive strengths and minor weaknesses is a morale exercise, not a strategic one.",
      "why": "All four components are required. Strengths and weaknesses are internal. Opportunities and threats are external. The framework only produces strategic insight when all four are considered and when the interactions between them are examined — how strengths can capture opportunities, how weaknesses expose the organization to threats. The list alone is descriptive. The analysis of interactions is where strategy emerges.",
